name: Amera Guffey
text:
I told my friend that i was having a very hard time coping with the death of my mom, so my friend told me to find god.
I went to church expecting to find god and be healed but what i discovered was much worse. I suspect church is a cult! Especially this one!!! they were dunking a baby under water! and when i screamed for them to stop People started yelling at me!!! In the beginning of this horrid experience a man came on stage wearing a black dress and started yelling!! And then women came on stage and started Singing and then bright lights were coming and flashing and people started crying and standing and yelling and raising there hand!!! when i tried to tell my friend she started laughing at me!! 0/10 do not recommend

name: Nicholas Papa
text: The place has a sign in front that says it's open from 10 to 4 on Tuesdays and I went there and every door was locked. Every single door. It looked like no one is here. Don't waste your time driving here. It's completely inaccessible. What the hell.

name: Alan Beckham
text:
Beautiful artwork and architecture.  Well worth the time.  Open Tuesday through Friday 9am - ?
No admission fee.  Offerings accepted but not solicited.

name: Ginny Phillips Allen
text: Original artwork in many larger-than-life Biblical portraits painted by three Greek painters brought in from the old country. Ornate brass and carved wood, starred blue ceiling. Tour guide is Malbis descendant who is on site Tues. - Sat. Free, donations welcomed.

name: Beau Stewart
text: Stunning. Open to the public. See it. Sit quietly for a minute and feel peace. It's fine to take pictures, and you'll want to do so.

name: Ryan Karkkainen
text: Strikingly beautiful inside and out. Friendly and welcoming. A stunning and humbling tribute.

name: Billie Lucas
text: The church is beautiful and so peaceful

name: Barbara Bush
text: When you open the large doors, you feel the dedication, devotion and love for God

name: Al Lipscomb
text: Although lightly attended due to the virus, a  warm and welcoming congregation was present for the Sunday services (Matins and Divine Liturgy).

name: Dorothy Priest
text: Very beautiful.  We attended the annual food festival.  Delicious!

name: Nicholas Wilson
text: Wonderful parish led by Father Ioannis, extremely welcoming.
